1
00:00:16,174 --> 00:00:19,810
Ned: All right, here he is.
We have visitor in the house.

2
00:00:19,835 --> 00:00:22,235
He's coming down, Felix.

3
00:00:22,260 --> 00:00:23,326
Come on.

4
00:00:24,449 --> 00:00:26,116
Scope down.

5
00:00:26,141 --> 00:00:28,909
Captain, here's the man
you were looking for.

6
00:00:32,457 --> 00:00:33,991
That's you, eh?

7
00:00:35,470 --> 00:00:37,338
Thought you'd be uglier.

8
00:00:37,363 --> 00:00:38,829
How did you get a submarine?

9
00:00:38,854 --> 00:00:41,654
[Chuckles] Yeah.

10
00:00:41,778 --> 00:00:43,244
Bit of a fluke, really.

11
00:00:43,269 --> 00:00:45,340
I was coxswain on her
less than six months ago.

12
00:00:45,365 --> 00:00:47,371
- Believe that?
- But then...

13
00:00:47,373 --> 00:00:49,506
Watch it. Sorry, mate.

14
00:00:49,531 --> 00:00:51,183
Then...

15
00:00:51,544 --> 00:00:53,944
That lovely little germ stowed away

16
00:00:53,946 --> 00:00:55,612
in some lieutenant's lungs.

17
00:00:55,614 --> 00:00:58,885
Next thing we know, the whole
crew were droppin' like flies.

18
00:00:58,910 --> 00:01:03,420
But me and me brother, no. Not us.

19
00:01:03,596 --> 00:01:07,569
Blessed with the gene. Kept us safe.

20
00:01:07,593 --> 00:01:09,493
Two weeks on,

21
00:01:09,518 --> 00:01:11,738
this little puppy...

22
00:01:11,931 --> 00:01:13,831
We have it all to ourselves.

23
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:17,526
"You're a lucky old git, Sean
Ramsey," I says to myself.

24
00:01:17,551 --> 00:01:20,537
But then... Then... Then...

25
00:01:20,562 --> 00:01:22,462
[Lowered voice] I had myself...

26
00:01:23,985 --> 00:01:26,420
My moment of revelation.

27
00:01:26,445 --> 00:01:28,035
I did.

28
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:30,994
It came to me

29
00:01:31,019 --> 00:01:32,736
there weren't no luck in it.

30
00:01:33,015 --> 00:01:35,135
This here,

31
00:01:35,739 --> 00:01:39,416
this plague and all, ain't no accident.

32
00:01:39,441 --> 00:01:42,259
Oh, yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

33
00:01:42,284 --> 00:01:44,784
- Design, mate.
- Yeah.

34
00:01:45,156 --> 00:01:47,120
That's what this is.

35
00:01:47,154 --> 00:01:48,754
- Mm-hmm.
- Design.

36
00:01:49,554 --> 00:01:51,712
Yeah.

37
00:01:52,586 --> 00:01:55,116
So, all's I had to do then

38
00:01:55,141 --> 00:01:57,944
was find a few people like us.

39
00:01:57,969 --> 00:01:59,276
- Immunes.
- Right.

40
00:01:59,278 --> 00:02:01,647
Train a crew to help me run this thing.

41
00:02:01,672 --> 00:02:05,883
Found quite a few as it happens,
some with military know-how.

42
00:02:05,885 --> 00:02:08,252
- The Max.
- That's right, Guv.

43
00:02:08,277 --> 00:02:10,687
Got Meself this, uh... This...

44
00:02:10,712 --> 00:02:11,977
[Paper rustles]

45
00:02:12,057 --> 00:02:14,291
Motley crew.

46
00:02:14,316 --> 00:02:17,460
They're kind of an ugly bunch. [Chuckles]

47
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,906
Don't be fooled.

48
00:02:18,931 --> 00:02:21,373
This lot here are some
of the nastiest fighters

49
00:02:21,398 --> 00:02:23,133
from the four corners of Europe.

50
00:02:23,158 --> 00:02:25,120
Ain't that right, Bruv?

51
00:02:25,563 --> 00:02:27,297
Open your mouth.

52
00:02:27,322 --> 00:02:30,056
Why?

53
00:02:30,081 --> 00:02:31,347
'Cause I said so.

54
00:02:31,372 --> 00:02:32,484
- [Smacks]
- [Grunts]

55
00:02:32,509 --> 00:02:34,042
- [Gun cocks]
- Ned! Ned!

56
00:02:34,067 --> 00:02:36,824
I don't like you. You double-crossed us.

57
00:02:36,849 --> 00:02:38,430
Put the gun away.

58
00:02:38,455 --> 00:02:39,587
The man's our guest

59
00:02:39,612 --> 00:02:41,016
and he's gonna sort through the crap

60
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:43,174
we pulled off the hospital ship.

61
00:02:46,078 --> 00:02:47,712
I don't trust him.

62
00:02:47,737 --> 00:02:50,638
I don't care.

63
00:02:52,352 --> 00:02:54,353
He's our guest.

64
00:02:58,783 --> 00:03:00,985
Still nothing on sonar, sir.

65
00:03:01,010 --> 00:03:02,214
If they're submerged

66
00:03:02,239 --> 00:03:03,972
on the opposite side of the Northern Bank,

67
00:03:04,216 --> 00:03:05,782
we'll see them as soon
as we're far enough south

68
00:03:05,807 --> 00:03:07,089
to peer behind it.

69
00:03:07,114 --> 00:03:09,047
How soon are we clear of the bank?

70
00:03:09,072 --> 00:03:11,873
Just another moment, sir.

71
00:03:11,898 --> 00:03:13,631
Woman: X.O. on the bridge.

72
00:03:13,656 --> 00:03:15,306
Sir?

73
00:03:16,306 --> 00:03:18,139
Anything?

74
00:03:18,422 --> 00:03:23,405
Only one thing I hate more than
seeing a submarine on sonar.

75
00:03:23,547 --> 00:03:24,746
What's that?

76
00:03:24,771 --> 00:03:27,605
Not seeing one.

77
00:03:31,062 --> 00:03:33,343
There's nothing behind the bank, sir.

78
00:03:34,472 --> 00:03:36,373
They must've hightailed it outta here.

79
00:03:36,375 --> 00:03:38,609
Yeah, but why? Where?

80
00:03:38,611 --> 00:03:40,298
Maybe our prisoner can enlighten us.

81
00:03:40,323 --> 00:03:41,542
He conscious?

82
00:03:41,567 --> 00:03:43,761
Weak, but conscious.

83
00:03:44,388 --> 00:03:47,189
I'd say go easy on him,

84
00:03:47,214 --> 00:03:49,761
but I wouldn't really mean it.

85
00:03:50,108 --> 00:03:51,909
Aye-aye.

86
00:03:53,768 --> 00:03:56,770
Sir? This sub...

87
00:03:56,795 --> 00:04:00,261
Are we hunting or evading it?

88
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:02,662
Both.

89
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:07,315
♪♪

