00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:32,712
and based on, uh, how much
louder they're getting, sir,

258
00:11:32,737 --> 00:11:35,460
I'd say they're heading... 0-7-5.

259
00:11:35,485 --> 00:11:37,041
Ballpark C.P.A.?

260
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:40,041
Closest point of approach would be, um...

261
00:11:42,908 --> 00:11:44,588
We're near collision course now, sir.

262
00:11:44,613 --> 00:11:47,087
[Radio chatter]

263
00:11:47,622 --> 00:11:49,321
We don't know if he's seen us yet.

264
00:11:54,665 --> 00:11:56,387
[Beeps]

265
00:11:56,412 --> 00:11:58,512
Bridge, captain.

266
00:11:58,568 --> 00:12:00,168
<i>Try 20 degrees starboard.</i>

267
00:12:00,193 --> 00:12:02,087
20 degrees starboard, aye.

268
00:12:02,112 --> 00:12:03,579
See if he's paying attention.

269
00:12:04,676 --> 00:12:08,387
[Whirring]

270
00:12:20,635 --> 00:12:22,932
[Sonar pinging steadily]

271
00:12:43,673 --> 00:12:47,072
They're turning, too, sir.
They're turning to intercept.

272
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:52,275
Ned: You see that?

273
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,781
They're turning 'cause they see us.

274
00:12:53,806 --> 00:12:55,539
They're running. That's them. I know.

275
00:12:55,564 --> 00:12:56,735
What are you waitin' for?!

276
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,626
Mind your P's and Q's, Ned.

277
00:12:59,490 --> 00:13:01,892
Sir, if he's an <i>Astute</i>
class, he's carrying a Spearfish,

278
00:13:01,917 --> 00:13:03,422
which means we're already in his range.

279
00:13:03,447 --> 00:13:04,847
I am aware of that.

280
00:13:04,872 --> 00:13:06,705
How long until we can hit him?

281
00:13:07,715 --> 00:13:10,821
At the rate we're closing,
almost another half hour.

282
00:13:12,042 --> 00:13:13,821
Are you expecting him to fire, sir?

283
00:13:13,846 --> 00:13:15,622
Not if he wants the cure.

284
00:13:15,647 --> 00:13:16,821
We don't want anything from him.

285
00:13:16,846 --> 00:13:19,013
We could fire first once we're in range.

286
00:13:19,038 --> 00:13:21,321
The instant we fire, we
give up our exact position.

287
00:13:21,346 --> 00:13:24,622
I know, sir, but what's the alternative?

288
00:13:27,911 --> 00:13:29,847
I'm working on it.

289
00:13:30,177 --> 00:13:32,847
We'll be in their fire range
in less than 30 minutes.

290
00:13:32,872 --> 00:13:35,247
Get your finger out! Come on!

291
00:13:36,042 --> 00:13:37,308
Well, you heard him.

292
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:38,930
Let's blow their asses out the water.

293
00:13:38,955 --> 00:13:41,322
We need to get closer so as
we can pick up Juan Carlos.

294
00:13:41,337 --> 00:13:44,655
What? For all we know, Juan Carlos is dead.

295
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:45,773
The way he was shot up,

296
00:13:45,775 --> 00:13:47,383
how's he supposed to
get off the ship anyway?

297
00:13:47,408 --> 00:13:48,382
He'll find a way.

298
00:13:48,407 --> 00:13:50,373
We don't even know if he's loyal!

299
00:13:50,398 --> 00:13:52,023
He could be sellin' us out,

300
00:13:52,048 --> 00:13:54,245
begging and groveling as we speak.

301
00:13:54,688 --> 00:13:57,993
It's not a question of loyalty, Ned.

302
00:13:58,018 --> 00:14:01,594
He's a believer, same as the rest of us.

303
00:14:03,171 --> 00:14:05,960
Your sub is closing on
us. What do they want?

304
00:14:05,985 --> 00:14:08,960
What do you mean? For the cure.
Are they gonna offer us a deal?

305
00:14:08,985 --> 00:14:11,660
No, no. They thought the
cure was on <i>Solace.</i>

306
00:14:11,685 --> 00:14:15,513
When... when we didn't find
it, the commander's brother,

307
00:14:15,538 --> 00:14:18,511
he became certain that
the cure was just a rumor.

308
00:14:18,536 --> 00:14:22,138
As far as they know, this is
just a floating warship, sir.

309
00:14:22,163 --> 00:14:24,511
[Coughs] So then why
are they comin' for us?

310
00:14:24,536 --> 00:14:27,737
[Breathes heavily] I don't know.

311
00:14:27,762 --> 00:14:29,336
It must be for revenge,

312
00:14:29,466 --> 00:14:31,047
for his men you killed on <i>Solace.</i>

313
00:14:31,072 --> 00:14:32,972
Not to rescue you?

314
00:14:33,149 --> 00:14:35,020
They don't care about me.

315
00:14:35,045 --> 00:14:36,845
He cares enough to avenge his other men.

316
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:39,210
You got the better of him.

317
00:14:39,235 --> 00:14:42,210
Now he needs to fix that.

318
00:14:42,575 --> 00:14:44,611
[Coughing]

319
00:14:44,636 --> 00:14:47,611
He's in range, hasn't fired
yet. What do you make of that?

320
00:14:48,478 --> 00:14:50,878
He knows you have countermeasures.

321
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:53,451
He wants to make sure he's
close enough to hit you.

322
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:55,774
Uh-huh. Pretty soon, he'll
be within <i>our</i> range.

323
00:14:55,799 --> 00:14:58,074
The insane fear nothing.

324
00:14:58,350 --> 00:15:03,117
Sir, I have been cooperative. Have I not?

325
00:15:03,142 --> 00:15:04,717
- I...
- [Handcuff clinks]

326
00:15:04,742 --> 00:15:06,942
May I make one request, please?

327
00:15:07,390 --> 00:15:09,963
I speak to you as one sailor to another.

328
00:15:09,988 --> 00:15:11,618
I am a man of honor.

329
00:15:11,861 --> 00:15:15,064
If they engage you, if
they want to sink you...

330
00:15:15,089 --> 00:15:18,657
and they most certainly will... [Coughs]

331
00:15:18,682 --> 00:15:22,263
I don't wanna drown like
this, handcuffed to a bed.

332
00:15:22,288 --> 00:15:23,915
I swear to you,

333
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:26,486
I won't jeopardize the safety of your ship.

334
00:15:26,743 --> 00:15:28,585
Take me outside.

335
00:15:28,610 --> 00:15:31,330
Above decks, please.

336
00:15:31,524 --> 00:15:34,592
I will tell you everything I know

337
00:15:34,617 --> 00:15:37,505
about every single member of that crew.

338
00:15:37,530 --> 00:15:39,063
[Coughs]

339
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,486
Slattery: If they wanted to negotiate,

340
00:15:40,511 --> 00:15:42,305
they're well within
range to reach out to us.

341
00:15:42,330 --> 00:15:45,305
Their bridge to bridge. Morse code, even.

342
00:15:45,330 --> 00:15:46,696
They're gonna try to sink us.

343
00:15:46,721 --> 00:15:48,305
We go to quiet two.

344
00:15:48,644 --> 00:15:51,384
Turn southeast toward
the North Bahama Bank.

345
00:15:51,417 --> 00:15:52,850
Even at dead slow,

346
00:15:52,875 --> 00:15:55,976
we may lose them just long
enough to get behind the shoal.

347
00:15:56,061 --> 00:15:58,387
If he chases us in the blind,

348
00:15:58,412 --> 00:16:00,985
we send our helo, drop a few
torpedoes down their throats.

349
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:03,978
Yeah, if he knows we've
slowed, he might just fire.

350
00:16:03,980 --> 00:16:07,087
At 4 knots, we'll have almost
no maneuverability to evade.

351
00:16:07,112 --> 00:16:08,287
You got a better move?

352
00:16:08,312 --> 00:16:10,626
Yeah, we fire first, take
our chances at a dogfight.

353
00:16:10,651 --> 00:16:12,525
You'd bet on me.

354
00:16:12,647 --> 00:16:14,666
Against a sub with Spearfish?

355
00:16:16,095 --> 00:16:18,662
Bet on you so far.

356
00:16:23,344 --> 00:16:27,314
[Radio chatter]

357
00:16:29,984 --> 00:16:32,652
[Indistinct conversations]

358
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:36,217
Alert all hands.

359
00:16:36,242 --> 00:16:38,090
We're going to quiet two.

360
00:16:38,115 --> 00:16:42,186
[Indistinct conversations continue]

361
00:16:42,211 --> 00:16:43,986
Yes, sir.

362
00:16:54,041 --> 00:16:56,406
All stations T.A.O.
We're going to quiet two.

363
00:16:56,431 --> 00:16:59,750
O.O.D. Helmsman, drop to 4 knots.

364
00:16:59,774 --> 00:17:02,546
[Beeping]

365
00:17:02,571 --> 00:17:04,947
All engines ahead one-third for 4 knots.

366
00:17:04,972 --> 00:17:08,247
[Whirring slows]

367
00:17:11,157 --> 00:17:13,947
Emcon Alpha set throughout the ship.

368
00:17:27,581 --> 00:17:28,915
[Beeps]

369
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:31,321
Now hear this...

370
00:17:32,592 --> 00:17:35,494
<i>This is the last 1mc
message for a while.</i>

371
00:17:35,519 --> 00:17:36,708
<i>As of this moment,</i>

372
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,099
we're going to quiet two,

373
00:17:38,124 --> 00:17:39,907
all personnel, quiet two.

374
00:17:39,932 --> 00:17:42,607
[Clanks, whirring slows]

375
00:17:42,632 --> 00:17:43,999
<i>You all know your jobs.</i>

376
00:17:44,024 --> 00:17:46,506
<i>We've drilled this
drill a hundred times.</i>

377
00:17:46,531 --> 00:17:50,566
<i>But a footstep could
give away our position.</i>

378
00:17:50,591 --> 00:17:54,306
This one's for real. Lock it down.

379
00:17:54,331 --> 00:17:56,406
<i>Ahead slow.</i>

380
00:17:56,431 --> 00:18:00,006
<i>Silence, fore and aft.</i>

381
00:18:02,050 --> 00:18:04,806
Chung: No talking or moving, okay?

382
00:18:05,787 --> 00:18:08,107
Don't talk, don't move
until further orders.

383
00:18:08,132 --> 00:18:09,607
Tight as a drum, guys.

384
00:18:09,632 --> 00:18:12,006
Nothing moves.

385
00:18:12,797 --> 00:18:15,607
Not even you. Down.

386
00:18:15,632 --> 00:18:18,607
- There you go. Just like Frankie taught you.
- [Whimpers]

387
00:18:18,632 --> 00:18:19,911
[Whispers] Stay.

388
00:18:42,268 --> 00:18:44,602
[Taps keys]

389
00:18:44,627 --> 00:18:48,264
I told you. I told you!
Look, what did I say?

390
00:18:48,289 --> 00:18:53,064
Now look at that. Nothing
there! Silent ship! Gone!

391
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:57,864
We should've taken the
shot! Now look at us!

392
00:19:00,688 --> 00:19:03,023
We should bloody well fire
off a dozen their ways.

393
00:19:03,048 --> 00:19:04,677
What? And hit 'em with dumb luck?

394
00:19:04,702 --> 00:19:06,177
And if we miss, what then?

395
00:19:06,202 --> 00:19:08,730
They killed seven of my men!

396
00:19:08,755 --> 00:19:11,856
Your men?<i>Your</i> men?

397
00:19:16,758 --> 00:19:19,081
How far to the Bahama
Bank, the North Shore?

398
00:19:19,106 --> 00:19:22,909
- 40 miles out, sir.
- Make a course, 0-3-0.

399
00:19:22,934 --> 00:19:24,500
Man: Right, 0-3-0.

400
00:19:24,525 --> 00:19:26,409
If he's going behind the island,

401
00:19:26,434 --> 00:19:28,634
- we'll meet him on the far side.
- Aye, sir.

402
00:19:28,659 --> 00:19:31,639
Patience, brother. Patience.

403
00:19:31,993 --> 00:19:35,094
His time will come.

404
00:19:55,703 --> 00:19:58,538
[Mouths words]

405
00:20:34,446 --> 00:20:36,927
[Exhales softly]

406
00:20:40,787 --> 00:20:45,026
- Sean: Is he back here, then?
- Man: Yes, sir. Hard at work.

407
00:20:45,124 --> 00:20:47,791
So, what'd you find?

408
00:20:47,816 --> 00:20:52,061
Well, the hospital ship was
the right place, as I thought.

409
00:20:52,086 --> 00:20:56,250
But it's a real pity that
your men had to run away

410
00:20:56,275 --> 00:20:58,075
before we got what we need.

411
00:20:58,903 --> 00:21:02,676
You are very fortunate
that I am here, you know?

412
00:21:02,701 --> 00:21:04,851
The Americans were preparing seriously

413
00:21:04,876 --> 00:21:06,351
for a delivery of the cure.

414
00:21:06,376 --> 00:21:07,551
We'll handle that.

415
00:21:07,576 --> 00:21:09,950
Yeah? What do you mean?

416
00:21:12,329 --> 00:21:13,763
[Coffeepot clatters]

417
00:21:13,788 --> 00:21:16,024
- We're gonna sink that Yankee ship.
- [Chuckles]

418
00:21:16,049 --> 00:21:17,648
How?

419
00:21:17,673 --> 00:21:21,024
Without a ship, their plans just collapse.

420
00:21:21,049 --> 00:21:23,492
What? No, I... that's...

421
00:21:23,517 --> 00:21:24,923
You said so yourself.

422
00:21:24,948 --> 00:21:27,391
Their captain is smart and dangerous,

423
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:30,091
so he won't surrender,
but he can't beat me,

424
00:21:30,116 --> 00:21:32,192
not in the open sea.

425
00:21:32,217 --> 00:21:34,591
His ship sinks.

426
00:21:35,643 --> 00:21:37,891
Hey, fret not.

427
00:21:37,916 --> 00:21:40,249
There'll be survivors.

428
00:21:40,274 --> 00:21:43,591
Maybe even that precious doctor of yours.

429
00:21:43,891 --> 00:21:46,591
If she's as important as you say,

430
00:21:46,616 --> 00:21:49,591
they'll put her on the first lifeboat.

431
00:21:49,616 --> 00:21:53,413
Uh, yeah, I suppose that's
true, but it's so risky.

432
00:21:53,471 --> 00:21:55,814
Not with my man on that ship.

433
00:21:56,307 --> 00:21:59,413
Special operator first class.

434
00:21:59,438 --> 00:22:03,540
That ship goes down,
he'll find a way off it.

435
00:22:03,565 --> 00:22:07,400
Make no mistake, we'll have what we need.

436
00:22:11,359 --> 00:22:13,487
Sir, are we allowed to
talk? [Inhales deeply]

437
00:22:13,512 --> 00:22:14,987
Yeah, sound dissipates in the air.

438
00:22:15,012 --> 00:22:17,087
Sub can't hear what's going on on deck.

439
00:22:17,112 --> 00:22:20,087
[Sniffs, exhales]

440
00:22:21,211 --> 00:22:24,886
We are going much slower,
yes? Running more quiet?

441
00:22:24,911 --> 00:22:26,386
[Sneezes, coughs]

442
00:22:27,358 --> 00:22:29,686
Here. No, gracias.

443
00:22:30,021 --> 00:22:32,386
- [Continues coughing]
- I know you smoke.

444
00:22:32,411 --> 00:22:34,611
Seen your nicotine-stained fingers.

445
00:22:35,056 --> 00:22:36,886
Smelled your clothes.

446
00:22:36,918 --> 00:22:38,831
Just... [exhales sharply]

447
00:22:38,856 --> 00:22:41,190
Just some water, please.

448
00:22:41,776 --> 00:22:44,644
- [Coughing]
- Unh-unh.

449
00:22:47,829 --> 00:22:51,531
[Stifles cough, exhales sharply]

450
00:22:51,556 --> 00:22:55,491
[Continues coughing]

451
00:22:55,516 --> 00:22:57,817
[Gargles, spits]

452
00:22:57,842 --> 00:22:59,766
Water for information.

453
00:23:00,225 --> 00:23:02,926
[Coughing]

454
00:23:03,069 --> 00:23:05,766
What more do you want to know?

455
00:23:05,791 --> 00:23:07,865
What's our range?

456
00:23:08,138 --> 00:23:10,639
[Sonar pinging steadily]

457
00:23:10,664 --> 00:23:12,697
I put them...

458
00:23:15,650 --> 00:23:17,467
Just inside 40 miles, sir.

459
00:23:17,491 --> 00:23:19,524
Gator: Sir, they've turned North.

460
00:23:19,549 --> 00:23:21,666
They're moving to the same
side of the bank as we are.

461
00:23:21,691 --> 00:23:24,065
Must've figured we were trying
to put the shoal between us.

462
00:23:24,090 --> 00:23:25,558
Sir, we won't get any of
the bank between us now

463
00:23:25,583 --> 00:23:26,857
unless we increase our speed.

464
00:23:26,882 --> 00:23:29,256
Sir, if we increase our
speed, they'll hear us.

465
00:23:30,544 --> 00:23:32,745
Just a few more minutes.

466
00:23:34,015 --> 00:23:36,456
And how did you all avoid being infected?

467
00:23:36,481 --> 00:23:39,456
[Coughing]

468
00:23:39,719 --> 00:23:42,756
I've told you so much information already.

469
00:23:42,781 --> 00:23:45,157
Please, give me some water.

470
00:23:45,221 --> 00:23:47,902
- [Breathing heavily]
- Come on.

471
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:53,130
[Panting]

472
00:23:53,155 --> 00:23:54,922
[Spits]

473
00:23:54,947 --> 00:23:56,296
[Gagging]

474
00:23:56,321 --> 00:24:00,195
What's going on with
you? What are you doing?

475
00:24:00,220 --> 00:24:02,596
There must've been something inside him.

476
00:24:02,621 --> 00:24:04,096
That's why he's bleeding.

477
00:24:04,121 --> 00:24:05,902
- [Continues gagging]
- That's why he was holding his chest.

478
00:24:05,927 --> 00:24:09,441
That's why he wanted up
on deck. Must be a beacon.

479
00:24:09,466 --> 00:24:11,425
- What do you got in there, huh? A little homing device?
- [Groaning]

480
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:12,716
Is that what that is?!

481
00:24:12,741 --> 00:24:14,974
There's nothing you can do about it now.

482
00:24:14,999 --> 00:24:16,927
My people know exactly where you are.

483
00:24:16,952 --> 00:24:19,230
Oh, they're <i>your</i>
people now? Is that right?

484
00:24:19,255 --> 00:24:21,656
Yeah. My people.

485
00:24:21,681 --> 00:24:25,930
We have already taken Europe, all of it.

486
00:24:26,281 --> 00:24:28,930
The people like me.

487
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:30,535
[Gasps]

488
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:34,630
On my ship, they all... Like me.

489
00:24:34,655 --> 00:24:37,556
[Gags] All... Like me.

490
00:24:37,581 --> 00:24:39,130
<i>Sobreviveremos.</i>

491
00:24:39,155 --> 00:24:42,731
<i>Sobreviveremos.</i> [Gasps]

492
00:24:46,771 --> 00:24:49,774
[Gasping, speaking Spanish]

493
00:24:49,799 --> 00:24:51,473
No! [Groans]

494
00:24:51,896 --> 00:24:54,774
[Grunting]

495
00:25:06,613 --> 00:25:09,666
- What's going on here?
- [Whooshing]

496
00:25:10,148 --> 00:25:12,339
- [Groans]
- Rios: You're right.

497
00:25:12,365 --> 00:25:13,998
There's something there.
It's causing damage.

498
00:25:14,023 --> 00:25:15,910
We have to open him up.
You're the most qualified.

499
00:25:16,690 --> 00:25:18,479
- What? Here?
- Can't take him below decks,

500
00:25:18,504 --> 00:25:20,363
not while he's thrashing around like that.

501
00:25:20,388 --> 00:25:21,933
- Sedating him.
- Aah!

502
00:25:21,958 --> 00:25:24,667
- Shh! Quiet!
- I'm not in the habit of operating on somebody

503
00:25:24,692 --> 00:25:26,403
who's clearly resistant to help.

504
00:25:26,428 --> 00:25:28,428
I'm not even sure that it's legal!

505
00:25:28,453 --> 00:25:30,720
Legal? According to who?

506
00:25:30,852 --> 00:25:33,786
He could've been broadcasting
to an enemy sub this whole time.

507
00:25:33,811 --> 00:25:36,603
Blood pressure's dropping.
Pulse is 125 and weak.

508
00:25:36,628 --> 00:25:37,861
He's bleeding internally now.

509
00:25:37,886 --> 00:25:39,552
Well, looks like he's gonna die anyway.

510
00:25:39,577 --> 00:25:41,477
Why we wasting our time
trying to cut it out of him?

511
00:25:41,502 --> 00:25:42,738
We should just throw him overboard.

512
00:25:42,763 --> 00:25:44,362
That certainly would be the
most expedient thing to do.

513
00:25:44,387 --> 00:25:46,902
All right, all right, I will do it.

514
00:25:47,696 --> 00:25:49,529
- Where's the equipment?
- I'll get it.

515
00:25:49,554 --> 00:25:52,828
Rachel: Let's move him. Need some help.

516
00:26:00,257 --> 00:26:03,125
[Mouths words]

517
00:26:35,066 --> 00:26:36,934
Rios: Do you see it?

518
00:26:36,959 --> 00:26:38,086
Rachel: Not yet.

519
00:26:38,874 --> 00:26:40,740
It's an incredibly large bleed.

520
00:26:41,116 --> 00:26:43,186
We don't have time to blood type him.

521
00:26:43,751 --> 00:26:46,590
We have a universal blood donor on board?

522
00:26:46,638 --> 00:26:49,597
Somebody with O-Negative blood?

523
00:26:51,856 --> 00:26:53,600
Hell, he can have my damn kidney

524
00:26:53,625 --> 00:26:55,258
if it'll get that thing
out of there any quicker.

525
00:26:55,283 --> 00:26:57,049
Give me a needle.

526
00:26:57,074 --> 00:27:00,109
Where is he? How many miles out?

527
00:27:00,134 --> 00:27:01,900
Mason: I put them...

528
00:27:01,925 --> 00:27:03,692
[Pinging continues steadily]

529
00:27:03,743 --> 00:27:05,709
Just inside 40 miles, sir.

530
00:27:06,109 --> 00:27:10,645
And that beacon could
easily have a 30-mile range.

531
00:27:11,470 --> 00:27:15,373
- Green deck. Get the helo in the air.
- Yes, sir.

532
00:27:19,304 --> 00:27:22,632
Bridge, set flight
quarters. Helo's cleared.

533
00:27:22,657 --> 00:27:23,889
Green deck.

534
00:27:23,914 --> 00:27:28,385
[Helicopter blades whirring, radio chatter]

535
00:27:29,149 --> 00:27:32,541
[Radio chatter continues]

536
00:27:33,456 --> 00:27:37,340
T.A.O., have bridge come to course 0-1-0.

537
00:27:37,365 --> 00:27:38,631
T.A.O.I.

538
00:27:39,015 --> 00:27:41,541
North, sir? For open water?

539
00:27:41,566 --> 00:27:43,399
Let's see if we can do
it without him hearing.

540
00:27:44,305 --> 00:27:46,073
T.A.O.,

541
00:27:46,193 --> 00:27:48,593
5-degree increments,

542
00:27:48,829 --> 00:27:51,497
10 to 15 seconds apart,

543
00:27:51,522 --> 00:27:53,241
randomly.

544
00:27:53,266 --> 00:27:55,041
Yes, sir.

545
00:27:55,866 --> 00:27:59,200
We might just sound like those porpoises.

546
00:27:59,781 --> 00:28:02,241
Rachel: It's punctured the esophagus.

547
00:28:02,985 --> 00:28:05,986
Currently lodged in the wall
of the lower left carotid,

548
00:28:06,011 --> 00:28:08,062
just about the union
at the ascending aorta.

549
00:28:08,087 --> 00:28:10,066
We need to get a suture in the artery wall

550
00:28:10,091 --> 00:28:12,866
before we remove it or he'll
die as soon as it comes out.

551
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:16,459
Number 6 suture on a 5-inch hemostat.

552
00:28:16,484 --> 00:28:18,866
Bayonet forceps.

553
00:28:20,278 --> 00:28:21,878
Thank you.

554
00:28:21,903 --> 00:28:24,515
Man: We're not doing nothing
if I can't hear shite!

555
00:28:24,540 --> 00:28:26,277
Max: Why don't you grow a set, would you?

556
00:28:26,302 --> 00:28:27,784
We fire now, he won't...

557
00:28:27,809 --> 00:28:30,017
At what? Fire at what, you moppet?

558
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:32,476
- Are you...
- I said shut it! Shut it!

559
00:28:32,774 --> 00:28:34,340
There's still a chain of command here!

560
00:28:34,365 --> 00:28:36,466
Enough! I don't want to hear any more

561
00:28:36,491 --> 00:28:39,127
of your bloody squawking, all right?

562
00:28:39,152 --> 00:28:41,785
Now, what are the options? Sonar?

563
00:28:41,873 --> 00:28:43,181
Still no signal on passive.

564
00:28:43,206 --> 00:28:46,060
Weapons? Armed, loaded, ready to fire.

565
00:28:46,084 --> 00:28:47,755
Why don't we hear 'em?
Have they dead stopped?

566
00:28:47,780 --> 00:28:49,318
Let's go active sonar.

567
00:28:49,342 --> 00:28:52,145
- He'll hear us.
- What choice do we have?

568
00:28:52,285 --> 00:28:55,887
If you ask me, they could
be bloody hearing us now.

569
00:28:56,935 --> 00:28:59,807
How fast can you target once we go active?

570
00:28:59,832 --> 00:29:03,211
Less than one minute, sir.
You have my word on that.

571
00:29:07,102 --> 00:29:08,970
Go active sonar.

572
00:29:10,307 --> 00:29:11,975
Going active.

573
00:29:12,008 --> 00:29:13,541
[Submarine clanks]

574
00:29:15,082 --> 00:29:18,084
- Sir, they've gone active. We're getting pinged.
- [Siren blaring]

575
00:29:18,109 --> 00:29:19,105
They're turning at us.

576
00:29:19,969 --> 00:29:22,136
Bridge, all ahead, flank 3. Evasive action.

577
00:29:22,165 --> 00:29:23,470
Engage prairie masker air.

578
00:29:23,495 --> 00:29:25,126
T.A.O., three fish in the water now!

579
00:29:25,151 --> 00:29:27,407
Clear to starboard! Sonar,
calculating firing solution.

580
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:28,976
Fire torpedoes down established bearings!

581
00:29:29,001 --> 00:29:30,657
- Solve for second salvo.
- Yes, sir!

582
00:29:30,682 --> 00:29:33,950
[Alarm beeping]

583
00:29:37,905 --> 00:29:40,582
[Torpedo whooshes]

584
00:29:44,555 --> 00:29:45,788
What was that?

585
00:29:45,984 --> 00:29:48,452
That was our torpedos.

586
00:29:48,477 --> 00:29:50,260
Second salvo, give 'em another three.

587
00:29:50,285 --> 00:29:51,784
Sonar, what's incoming?

588
00:29:51,809 --> 00:29:53,476
He's at full speed now, sir,
headed straight for us...

589
00:29:53,501 --> 00:29:56,260
He's fired, sir! Just fired two!

590
00:29:57,657 --> 00:30:00,673
Now three! Now four, sir!
He's fired four! Four incoming!

591
00:30:00,698 --> 00:30:02,264
Bridge, torpedoes inbound!

592
00:30:02,289 --> 00:30:06,661
Circle back over our wake
and point the ship 2-2-5!

593
00:30:10,445 --> 00:30:14,502
[Torpedoes whoosh]

594
00:30:16,872 --> 00:30:21,208
Active return, bearing 2-7-5!
We've got incoming torpedoes!

595
00:30:21,297 --> 00:30:24,702
Fire again, sir? I have a
point of origin. We can get 'em.

596
00:30:24,727 --> 00:30:27,327
- Hell, no! Dive!
- All hands, crash dive!

597
00:30:27,352 --> 00:30:29,619
- Turn it all off!
- Ian: Make fast gear and crew!

598
00:30:29,644 --> 00:30:31,702
Helm, 35 degrees hard starboard!

599
00:30:31,727 --> 00:30:33,405
- [Alarm blaring]
- Dive, dive, dive!

600
00:30:33,430 --> 00:30:36,105
It's too shallow here,
sir! We'll hit bottom!

601
00:30:39,718 --> 00:30:44,429
[Alarm continues blaring]

602
00:30:48,581 --> 00:30:50,882
[Whooshing]

603
00:30:50,907 --> 00:30:54,008
Incoming torpedoes range 500 yards!

604
00:30:54,756 --> 00:30:57,828
400 yards! All hands, brace for impact!

605
00:30:57,853 --> 00:31:00,229
[Radio chatter]

606
00:31:02,678 --> 00:31:04,872
300! Bridge, you see the trails.

607
00:31:04,897 --> 00:31:06,697
Call it if they're gonna hit!

608
00:31:06,699 --> 00:31:08,065
200 yards!

609
00:31:08,067 --> 00:31:10,729
[Torpedo whooshing]

610
00:31:17,835 --> 00:31:19,502
We're clear!

611
00:31:19,527 --> 00:31:22,124
Man: That's the last fish. Last
fish clear, last fish clear.

612
00:31:24,804 --> 00:31:27,473
[Radio chatter]

613
00:31:27,498 --> 00:31:29,364
Mason: Sir?

614
00:31:29,389 --> 00:31:31,733
He's stopping pinging. He's gone silent.

615
00:31:31,758 --> 00:31:32,624
Did we hit him?

616
00:31:32,649 --> 00:31:34,649
I don't know, sir. He's...

617
00:31:35,777 --> 00:31:37,778
He's just gone.

618
00:31:38,531 --> 00:31:42,499
Stand by for my confirmation.
No, no, there's still silence.

619
00:31:46,793 --> 00:31:49,477
Chandler: Did any of them
sound like hits to you?

620
00:31:49,502 --> 00:31:51,875
I can't be sure, sir.

621
00:31:52,115 --> 00:31:54,875
If I'd heard any secondaries,
I'd know, but this...

622
00:31:54,941 --> 00:31:57,141
It's just not enough information.

623
00:31:57,393 --> 00:31:58,826
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Hey.

624
00:31:58,867 --> 00:32:01,368
We're still here.

625
00:32:02,646 --> 00:32:05,066
You did your job.

626
00:32:06,219 --> 00:32:10,701
But if we didn't hit it, where did it go?

627
00:32:18,282 --> 00:32:21,807
[Rattling]

628
00:32:24,301 --> 00:32:25,969
[Rumbling]

629
00:32:26,237 --> 00:32:28,003
What the hell is that?

630
00:32:28,028 --> 00:32:31,117
We're scraping the canyon walls.

631
00:32:31,212 --> 00:32:33,715
[Rattle]

632
00:32:36,237 --> 00:32:37,904
[Scraping continues]

633
00:32:37,929 --> 00:32:39,647
Bloody hell.

634
00:32:39,672 --> 00:32:42,368
My God, the hull's gonna buckle!

635
00:32:50,234 --> 00:32:53,603
Nerve, men. Show some nerve.

636
00:32:53,628 --> 00:32:56,796
[Rattling continues]

637
00:32:56,821 --> 00:32:59,122
Courageous make their own luck.

638
00:32:59,758 --> 00:33:03,786
Never forget, we're the selected.

639
00:33:08,041 --> 00:33:11,482
[Squishing]

640
00:33:11,794 --> 00:33:13,462
I'm not exactly sure

641
00:33:13,487 --> 00:33:16,486
this is precisely what
you were looking for.

642
00:33:17,453 --> 00:33:21,389
It's a... Flash drive.

643
00:33:22,399 --> 00:33:24,000
Not a beacon.

644
00:33:26,942 --> 00:33:29,182
Bring up V.M.S. on the monitor.

645
00:33:29,207 --> 00:33:30,973
[Radio chatter]

646
00:33:31,103 --> 00:33:34,393
Okay, there's a very
narrow canyon here, sir.

647
00:33:34,418 --> 00:33:35,749
It's big enough for a sub

648
00:33:35,774 --> 00:33:37,641
that could do an emergency dive there?

649
00:33:37,861 --> 00:33:40,196
Into that? Blind at 20 knots?

650
00:33:40,221 --> 00:33:42,627
He's not a Royal Navy
captain. He's a wild card.

651
00:33:42,692 --> 00:33:44,992
Unless he knows how to helm a sub,

652
00:33:45,017 --> 00:33:47,684
he'll crack up along that canyon wall.

653
00:33:47,803 --> 00:33:49,503
[Door opens]

654
00:33:49,900 --> 00:33:52,062
It wasn't a beacon.

655
00:33:52,087 --> 00:33:54,354
[Panting]

656
00:33:54,379 --> 00:33:56,879
[Flash drive clicks]

657
00:33:56,904 --> 00:34:00,307
- [Beep]
- Sir, these files are completely corrupted.

658
00:34:00,332 --> 00:34:02,332
It's been inside him for 12 hours.

659
00:34:02,357 --> 00:34:04,090
Can you retrieve the data?

660
00:34:04,115 --> 00:34:07,221
We'll try to interpolate,
sir. It's gonna take some time.

661
00:34:19,961 --> 00:34:22,471
Dr. Hunter.

662
00:34:22,805 --> 00:34:24,939
Dr. Hunter. Of course.

663
00:34:25,499 --> 00:34:27,705
Where do you think you're going?

664
00:34:27,842 --> 00:34:31,424
I have something that
your captain needs to see.

665
00:34:31,581 --> 00:34:34,824
Take me to the bridge now!

666
00:34:37,683 --> 00:34:39,862
I found it.

667
00:34:40,692 --> 00:34:42,959
Dr. Hunter. Her mentor.

668
00:34:42,984 --> 00:34:44,205
I know where he is.

669
00:34:44,230 --> 00:34:46,097
He'll know the locations.

670
00:34:56,765 --> 00:34:58,297
His blood pressure's dropping.

671
00:34:58,322 --> 00:35:01,661
We need to get him to the medical bay now.

672
00:35:06,431 --> 00:35:09,925
Classified burst transmission from the CDC.

673
00:35:10,779 --> 00:35:12,412
So he got it from <i>Solace.</i>

674
00:35:12,437 --> 00:35:14,404
I've got geographical coordinates.

675
00:35:14,406 --> 00:35:16,439
They'll be decrypted in a moment, sir.

676
00:35:17,608 --> 00:35:20,585
Alisha: 40-45-38

677
00:35:20,610 --> 00:35:23,677
and 111-53-27.

678
00:35:23,702 --> 00:35:25,269
That's Salt Lake City, sir.

679
00:35:25,294 --> 00:35:27,572
- Decrypting the next location.
- [Beeping]

680
00:35:27,597 --> 00:35:29,263
Slattery: Phoenix.

681
00:35:29,288 --> 00:35:31,221
It's the labs.

682
00:35:32,729 --> 00:35:34,329
It's <i>all</i> the labs.

683
00:35:34,354 --> 00:35:36,654
He didn't wanna be up on
deck to transmit our location.

684
00:35:36,679 --> 00:35:39,835
He wanted to be up there
so he could swim to the sub

685
00:35:39,860 --> 00:35:41,126
once they'd sunk us.

686
00:35:41,151 --> 00:35:43,135
He wanted to deliver that thing to them.

687
00:35:43,468 --> 00:35:46,036
They want the cure, all right,
but they want <i>all</i> the cure

688
00:35:46,038 --> 00:35:47,404
so they can control it.

689
00:35:47,406 --> 00:35:49,072
Chandler: That's why they
went to <i>Solace,</i>

690
00:35:49,074 --> 00:35:50,907
to find the location of the other labs.

691
00:35:50,909 --> 00:35:53,147
How are they gonna get to
the inland ones from a sub?

692
00:35:53,172 --> 00:35:54,771
Sir, I got something on radar.

693
00:35:54,796 --> 00:35:56,572
What is it?

694
00:35:56,597 --> 00:36:00,172
- [Beeping rapidly]
- T.A.O., ballistic missile fire detected.

695
00:36:00,197 --> 00:36:02,030
Missiles.

696
00:36:02,145 --> 00:36:04,212
Climbing, just came over the horizon.

697
00:36:04,237 --> 00:36:06,433
- Inbound?
- No, sir. They're diverging.

698
00:36:06,465 --> 00:36:09,249
Already pretty spread out.

699
00:36:11,215 --> 00:36:13,083
How many? I've got 16.

700
00:36:13,108 --> 00:36:14,808
Now 17, 18.

701
00:36:14,810 --> 00:36:16,896
- Gotta be coming from the sub.
- Those missiles are headed

702
00:36:16,921 --> 00:36:18,405
toward the same coordinates
I just pulled up.

703
00:36:18,430 --> 00:36:20,334
- They're bombing the labs.
- Son of a bitch.

704
00:36:20,359 --> 00:36:22,839
- T.A.O., calculate a target to intercept.
- Calculating, sir.

705
00:36:22,841 --> 00:36:25,793
Fire SM-3s to intercept. Where
is that sub? Is it in range?

706
00:36:25,818 --> 00:36:27,543
- It's too far, sir.
- Damn it.

707
00:36:27,568 --> 00:36:30,154
Batteries release on
every target you got now!

708
00:36:30,179 --> 00:36:32,238
Yes, sir. Batteries release on all tracks.

709
00:36:32,263 --> 00:36:35,676
Birds away, track 2-5-7-1,
2-5-7-2, 2-5-7-3.

710
00:36:35,701 --> 00:36:37,279
Slattery: Granderson, we
gotta get a message to the lab.

711
00:36:37,304 --> 00:36:38,575
We gotta get those people out of there.

712
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:44,737
[Missiles whooshing]

713
00:36:47,704 --> 00:36:49,372
Get out now.

714
00:36:49,397 --> 00:36:51,558
The lab you are will be under
missile attack within minutes.

715
00:36:51,583 --> 00:36:53,339
If you are hearing the sound of my voice

716
00:36:53,364 --> 00:36:55,925
and are located in any of
the labs listed on the CDC...

717
00:36:55,950 --> 00:36:58,889
If you are hearing me, get away
from the entire complex now!

718
00:36:58,914 --> 00:37:00,680
All staff, I want all staff 2 miles

719
00:37:00,705 --> 00:37:02,005
from your building immediately.

720
00:37:02,030 --> 00:37:04,196
All missiles now out of range, sir.

721
00:37:04,221 --> 00:37:05,887
How many we get?

722
00:37:05,912 --> 00:37:08,095
I have confirmation on...

723
00:37:09,552 --> 00:37:12,720
Two were in range, sir. We got them both.

724
00:37:12,839 --> 00:37:14,395
Out of how many?

725
00:37:14,420 --> 00:37:16,496
We logged 26.

726
00:37:18,028 --> 00:37:22,496
Virtually all of them were
out of range before we fired.

727
00:37:31,257 --> 00:37:34,553
I had him for a few
moments, but he slipped back.

728
00:37:34,578 --> 00:37:37,446
I tried everything I could.

729
00:37:39,541 --> 00:37:41,975
Why would they want to
destroy all the labs?

730
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:43,917
It doesn't make any sense.

731
00:37:43,942 --> 00:37:46,276
[Takes off gloves]

732
00:37:46,301 --> 00:37:48,668
Unless already have the vaccine.

733
00:37:48,788 --> 00:37:51,288
Maybe that's how they "conquered" Europe.

734
00:37:51,313 --> 00:37:52,617
Is that possible?

735
00:37:52,642 --> 00:37:55,617
I don't see how anyone could
have the primordial besides me.

736
00:37:55,943 --> 00:37:57,743
Europe was decimated.

737
00:37:57,768 --> 00:38:00,450
It was one of the hottest
zones thanks to Niels.

738
00:38:01,285 --> 00:38:03,453
But yes.

739
00:38:03,823 --> 00:38:06,166
I suppose it's possible.

740
00:38:06,769 --> 00:38:08,702
Slattery: He never asked for the cure.

741
00:38:08,727 --> 00:38:10,768
I figured it was 'cause he knew

742
00:38:10,793 --> 00:38:12,767
he was never getting off the ship.

743
00:38:13,958 --> 00:38:17,567
Maybe he'd already gotten
it. Maybe they all had.

744
00:38:18,231 --> 00:38:20,131
He kept saying,

745
00:38:20,156 --> 00:38:23,267
"everyone on my ship is like me."

746
00:38:32,087 --> 00:38:35,329
<i>The seals think it was a
Tomahawk missile or a bomb.</i>

747
00:38:35,354 --> 00:38:36,720
<i>We didn't see it, but we heard it.</i>

748
00:38:36,722 --> 00:38:38,221
<i>It was really, really loud, dad.</i>

749
00:38:38,223 --> 00:38:40,036
<i>Grandpa said it was
just over the horizon.</i>

750
00:38:40,061 --> 00:38:41,536
<i>Yeah. Who's doing this, daddy?</i>

751
00:38:41,561 --> 00:38:44,235
There are people who want to stop us.

752
00:38:44,423 --> 00:38:46,636
I know that's hard to believe,

753
00:38:46,661 --> 00:38:50,235
but looks like I'm gonna be gone
a lot longer than we thought.

754
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:53,317
<i>Do you think that we
need to move away?</i>

755
00:38:53,342 --> 00:38:55,976
<i>Kelly thought that maybe
it was a good idea.</i>

756
00:38:56,352 --> 00:38:58,485
<i>Yes, hi.</i>

757
00:38:58,510 --> 00:39:00,735
<i>Do you think we need
to move further inland?</i>

758
00:39:00,869 --> 00:39:02,768
As far as we can tell, you're safe there.

759
00:39:02,793 --> 00:39:05,661
These people wanted the labs. That's...

760
00:39:05,686 --> 00:39:07,819
Looks like it's all they wanted.

761
00:39:07,844 --> 00:39:08,843
<i>Why?</i>

762
00:39:08,868 --> 00:39:10,335
